# Rein configuration example.
#
# Copy this file to .env (which is gitignored) and fill in the values:
#   cp .env.example .env
#
# .env is loaded automatically by docker compose and by most shells via
# `set -a; source .env; set +a`. Never commit the real .env file.

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Required
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------

# Bearer token for the admin API. Anyone with this token can flip the
# kill-switch, mint virtual keys, and revoke them. Treat it like a root secret.
# Generate a fresh one with: openssl rand -hex 32
REIN_ADMIN_TOKEN=

# AES-256 key used to encrypt upstream API keys at rest in the SQLite keystore.
# 32 bytes, hex-encoded (64 hex characters). Rein refuses to start without
# this value when REIN_DB_URL points at a SQLite database, so plaintext
# credentials cannot land on disk by accident.
# Generate a fresh one with: openssl rand -hex 32
# Lose this key and the database becomes unreadable. Back it up like a root secret.
REIN_ENCRYPTION_KEY=

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Optional (defaults shown)
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------

# HTTP port Rein listens on.
# REIN_PORT=8080

# Keystore location. Supported schemes:
#   sqlite:<path>   durable on-disk store, AES-256-GCM encrypted at rest
#   memory          in-memory store, cleared on restart (tests / ephemeral use)
# REIN_DB_URL=sqlite:./rein.db

# Upstream base URLs. Override these to point Rein at a staging upstream,
# a local mock, or a sibling gateway that speaks the OpenAI or Anthropic API.
# REIN_OPENAI_BASE=https://api.openai.com
# REIN_ANTHROPIC_BASE=https://api.anthropic.com

# Operator-editable pricing overrides file (#25). If unset, Rein probes
# /etc/rein/rein.json first, then falls back to just the embedded pricing
# table. See docs/quickstart.md section 3b for the JSON format and for the
# Kubernetes ConfigMap pattern. Required if you want to add pricing for a
# provider-specific model (Groq's llama-3.3-70b-versatile, Fireworks, DeepSeek,
# etc.) so that daily_budget_usd and month_budget_usd caps actually fire on
# that key's spend.
# REIN_CONFIG_FILE=/etc/rein/rein.json

# Optional background poll interval for REIN_CONFIG_FILE. If set, Rein spawns a
# goroutine that stats the file on each tick and triggers a reload when mtime
# advances. Use this for Kubernetes ConfigMap deployments where sending SIGHUP
# to a pod requires kubectl exec. Leave unset for SIGHUP-only reload (the
# unix-native way: kill -HUP $(pidof rein), docker kill --signal=HUP rein,
# or systemctl reload rein). Duration in Go time.ParseDuration form; bounded
# to [1s, 1h]; out-of-range values fail at startup.
# REIN_CONFIG_POLL_INTERVAL=30s

# Expiry sweeper tick cadence (#77). Controls how often Rein auto-revokes
# keys whose expires_at has passed so the audit trail records
# revoked_at == expires_at. The proxy hot path always rejects expired
# keys regardless of this value, so tightening the interval only tightens
# the audit-trail drift. Duration in Go time.ParseDuration form; bounded
# to [10s, 1h]. Out-of-range or malformed values fail at startup.
# REIN_EXPIRY_SWEEP_INTERVAL=60s

# Graceful shutdown grace window (#76). On SIGTERM / SIGINT Rein flips a
# drain flag (new /v1/* return 503 draining) and gives in-flight LLM
# calls this much wall-clock to finish before net/http force-closes the
# remaining connections. Sized for reasoning-model tail latency; shorter
# values raise the number of force-closed requests during rolling
# deploys. Duration in Go time.ParseDuration form; bounded to [1s, 5m].
# Out-of-range or malformed values fail at startup. Set your Kubernetes
# terminationGracePeriodSeconds to at least this value + 5 so the pod
# has time to drain before SIGKILL.
# REIN_SHUTDOWN_GRACE=30s
